#define ManySingleMakefile

XCOMM Because some of the examples make direct call to either GLU, GL,
XCOMM or to the math library, we need to add "-lGL -lXm -lXt -lX11 -lm"
XCOMM to the link line to prevent multiple Makefiles. A user only needs
XCOMM to add a library to the link line if a programs makes direct calls
XCOMM to it.
XCOMM
#define OtherLibs -lGLU -lGL -lXm -lXt -lX11 -lm

#ifndef CreatingUserMakefile
TOP_OF_TREE = ../../../..
OTHERSOURCE = README
#endif

XCOMM The previous magic comment will cause the parallel make utility
XCOMM  'smake' to be used.
XCOMM ----------------------------------------------------------------------
XCOMM   Makefile for The Inventor Mentor examples - C++ version
XCOMM 
XCOMM   To make all the C++ examples, type:
XCOMM 	make
XCOMM 
XCOMM   To make a specfic C++ example, type:
XCOMM 
XCOMM 	make ch#.ex#.name
XCOMM 
XCOMM   where ch# is the chapter number from The Inventor Mentor
XCOMM        ex# is the example number from  "     "       "
XCOMM        name is a short name/description of the example
XCOMM 
XCOMM   For example,
XCOMM 	make 04.1.Cameras
XCOMM 
XCOMM ----------------------------------------------------------------------
XCOMM 

